WEBVTT

00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:04.301
PulseProof is a trusted second screen for World Cup fans.

00:00:04.301 --> 00:00:14.384
It turns verified live match data into spoiler-safe Catch-up, match communities, and non-transferable on-chain fan identity—before kickoff, during play, and after the final whistle.

00:00:16.100 --> 00:00:18.933
TxLINE is the primary live signal.

00:00:18.933 --> 00:00:25.070
PulseProof normalizes activated devnet fixtures and events into a public Server-Sent Events stream.

00:00:25.070 --> 00:00:37.346
The Live Center keeps World Cup competition labels, official team abbreviations, flags, live state, finished results, upcoming fixtures, stadiums and kickoff times in one source-labelled view.

00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:43.448
Finished matches remain fully replayable through the same interface used for live coverage.

00:00:43.448 --> 00:00:50.442
England versus Argentina shows the final two-one score, match pulse, scorer, cards, substitutions and source sequence numbers.

00:00:50.442 --> 00:00:54.967
Spoiler Shield hides results everywhere, including the road to the final.

00:00:54.967 --> 00:01:01.550
Catch-up reveals only the selected event prefix; signed relay and offline recap never expose future moments.

00:01:08.100 --> 00:01:13.114
Phantom stays connected while the user moves from Live Center to Fan Zone.

00:01:13.114 --> 00:01:18.514
The wallet-owned profile, display name, points, streak and inventory follow without a second connection.

00:01:20.100 --> 00:01:23.407
Profile editing creates a human-readable alias for match chat.

00:01:23.407 --> 00:01:29.285
The new name is prepared on the Fan Alias PDA, not stored as a browser-only preference.

00:01:30.100 --> 00:01:32.631
Phantom shows the real devnet transaction.

00:01:32.631 --> 00:01:42.334
After approval, the page updates immediately to Cryptovuive twenty-six, displays a confirmed receipt and Explorer link, and keeps the new alias after reload.

00:01:45.100 --> 00:01:47.042
Daily check-in uses Solana time.

00:01:47.042 --> 00:01:52.868
The interface previews seven streak days and disables duplicate claims within the same UTC day.

00:01:55.100 --> 00:01:57.757
One Phantom approval creates the check-in proof.

00:01:57.757 --> 00:02:05.348
The page immediately marks today complete, raises the streak and points, and shows a confirmed devnet receipt without any reload.

00:02:08.100 --> 00:02:14.916
The daily quiz draws five questions from ten thousand deterministic World Cup variations built from sourced facts.

00:02:14.916 --> 00:02:21.732
Answer links stay hidden, explanations appear only after selection, and this run scores five out of five.

00:02:21.732 --> 00:02:25.741
Daily rewards are single-use; practice rounds remain unlimited and reward-free.

00:02:36.100 --> 00:02:38.714
Phantom signs the authorized points claim.

00:02:38.714 --> 00:02:46.992
Seventy points arrive immediately, the button changes to Claimed today, and the transaction receipt remains independently verifiable on Explorer.

00:02:49.100 --> 00:02:56.786
The reward catalog contains thirty-six original, non-transferable medals, badges, avatar frames and characters, including clearly dated limited editions.

00:02:56.786 --> 00:03:01.056
We scroll through every item before randomly selecting Bolt Keeper.

00:03:01.056 --> 00:03:07.461
Prices are fixed by the on-chain catalog, so the client cannot invent a cheaper redemption.

00:03:17.100 --> 00:03:24.558
The transaction completes atomically: Bolt Keeper becomes owned and active, and the balance drops by one hundred sixty points.

00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:31.675
Chat belongs to each match, beside the live or replay timeline.

00:03:31.675 --> 00:03:37.913
The composer uses the on-chain alias and blocks links, betting, wallet secrets and anonymous impersonation.

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:43.788
Posting requires a fresh Phantom message signature, not a fee.

00:03:43.788 --> 00:03:49.414
After approval, the server verifies the wallet, alias, fixture and anti-replay nonce.

00:03:49.414 --> 00:03:55.040
The signed message appears instantly as Cryptovuive twenty-six in the England–Argentina room.

00:03:57.100 --> 00:04:01.709
Finally, Judge Room runs the product instead of trusting slides.

00:04:01.709 --> 00:04:15.536
Eight fresh checks validate production identity, the World Cup-only catalog, public SSE, spoiler isolation, a signed Catch-up Capsule, browser-side Ed25519 verification, the live Solana programs and the offline cache boundary.

00:04:15.536 --> 00:04:25.676
This run passes eight of eight and exposes current points, alias, finalized quiz and reward receipts, Explorer, CI and the public repository.

00:04:29.100 --> 00:04:33.426
PulseProof turns live context into community identity and verifiable memory.

00:04:33.426 --> 00:04:38.185
Before, during and after the match, every match leaves a memory.

